Got it üëç I see your code already sets focus on txtCardSerial after a tap (txtCardSerial_TextChanged) and after Page_Load.
But right now, when you click Tap In or Tap Out, it only updates the hidden field ‚Äî it doesn‚Äôt explicitly set focus back to txtCardSerial.

You just need to add a little JavaScript when the radio button changes. That way, after clicking In or Out, the cursor immediately goes back to the textbox.

Here‚Äôs the fix:

Update your existing JavaScript for the radio buttons:

<script type="text/javascript">
    // When user changes radio button, update hidden field and focus textbox
    document.querySelectorAll('input[name="tapMode"]').forEach(function (radio) {
        radio.addEventListener('change', function () {
            document.getElementById('<%= hfTapMode.ClientID %>').value = this.value;

            // ‚úÖ Set focus to txtCardSerial
            var txtCardSerial = document.getElementById('<%= txtCardSerial.ClientID %>');
            if (txtCardSerial) {
                txtCardSerial.focus();
            }
        });
    });

    // On page load, restore the radio button from hidden field
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
        var savedMode = document.getElementById('<%= hfTapMode.ClientID %>').value;

        if (!savedMode) {
            savedMode = "In"; // default
            document.getElementById('<%= hfTapMode.ClientID %>').value = savedMode;
        }

        // Uncheck all radios first
        document.querySelectorAll('input[name="tapMode"]').forEach(function (r) {
            r.checked = false;
        });

        // Check only the saved one
        var radioToCheck = document.getElementById("radio" + savedMode);
        if (radioToCheck) {
            radioToCheck.checked = true;
        }
    });
</script>


---

‚úÖ With this change:

If you click Tap In, focus jumps to txtCardSerial.

If you click Tap Out, focus also jumps to txtCardSerial.

After every tap (postback), your existing Page.SetFocus(txtCardSerial); in code-behind keeps it focused.



---

Do you also want me to make the Enter key automatically clear and re-focus txtCardSerial without triggering a full page reload? That would make the tapping smoother.

